args:
Urged on by Nedrick, the prince takes up the
tome. When he does, the book's radiance—
which glows only in response to one of royal
blood—fades. The prince then shapeshifts and
attempts to fight, but is defeated by Nedrick,
who moves to deliver the finishing blow.
I will defeat you, Brother... I must...\nUuurrgh...

His mind has been shattered by the mask.
Still, it was an impressive performance;
the wits of an ordinary man would have
fled the moment it was placed upon him.
Damn you! Why did you do this to him?!
Takes a real tough guy to use magic and\nmake someone else do his dirty work—\nso let's see how ya handle a REAL fight!
Worry not; I shall deal with the rest of\nyou anon. But for the moment...
The time has come to prove your supposed\nseventh scion false—a deed which can\neasily be done with the seal on this tome.
That glowing crest? What of it?
That crest is Aurelius's seal. It ensures\nnone but those of the royal bloodline\ncan behold the contents of this book.
When one of the royal family touches it,\nit responds to their blood and the seal\nis undone, causing the crest to shine.
Though the seal's power has been lost,\nthat mechanism yet remains intact.
You all saw with your own eyes how the\ncrest shone when I held aloft the book.
This serves as incontrovertible proof\nthat I am a member of the royal line.
Your words are as empty and hollow\nas your skull!
Let us put the truth of that to the test.\n...Zethia? Take up the book.
No! I refuse to be party to this game;\nI couldn't possibly test my brother so...
Your doubts betray you, else you would\nsurely take up the book without hesitation\nand prove {player_name} true.
That's not the case at all!\n...Very well. Give it to me.
And there we have our proof:\nZethia is of the royal line.
The time is nigh, {player_name}.\nTake the book in hand!
(This is it. This is how I prove\nmy bloodline for good.)
(I descend from King Alberius, and am the\nseventh child of my father, King Aurelius!)
(I carry the dragonblood! I can form pacts!)
(Yes! I knew I was... Oh no.)
No... NO! This can't be happening!
Now do you see? You are false.

If you remain unconvinced, place the book
in the hand of your fallen brother there.
I've no doubt it will spring to life for him,
even in his current grave condition.
However, the truth you wish to deny\nwill only grow more pronounced.
This...this is madness. If I'm not the\nseventh scion, then WHO AM I?!
And what if you were not royalty?

Say you were one of the smallfolk.
A base person of no real consequence.
And then, one day, people decided you
were not needed. What would you think?
Our discussion ends here. If you are not\nZethia's brother, there is no longer cause\nfor her to return with you.
Come, ＂sister.＂ I will be taking you\nto northern Grastaea.
Stop! Stooop! Zethia is my sister!\nI WON'T LET YOU TAKE HER!
Then you would use force to reclaim her?\nHeh. So be it. Come at me.
Entrusting your attacks to fury and rage\nalone will only bring about defeat.
SHUT UP! I WON'T LET YOU DO THIS!\nGIVE ME ZETHIA! GIVE HER TO ME!
H-he turned aside my darling in his\nshapeshifted form like it was nothing...
Okay, I've done enough standing on the\nsidelines—time to jump in and help out!
Hell yeah! Everybody back up the boss\nand... Wait, what the hell?!
I can't let you do that, Ranzaaaal...
Their struggle is between them alone;\nyou have no right to interfere.
How do you even think you can help out\nwhen you're SO DARN WEAK? Kya ha ha! \nOh, you guys are funny.

Prostrate yourselves and bear witness as
the ostentation of your ＂friendship＂ and
＂bonds＂ is swept aside by the tidal wave
that is reality.

With your composure fled, you would
attack with wanton abandon, trusting in
the power of your shapeshifting to see
the day won.
Your body is hale and healthy,\nyet this is all the ability you possess?
Alas, too long have you contented yourself\nwith your royal status and neglected the\ndiscipline required for improvement.

Your opposition to the Other?
The establishment of your kingdom?
These are burdens you simply foisted
upon those fool enough to support you.
I have no obligation to let such a wasted\nlife continue, and so shall dispatch you\nnow with all haste.
Stop! Think about this! There can be no\nmeaning in your taking my brother's life!
The weakling is a stain on existence;\nthat is reason enough.

It is over, false prince. And if you wish
to turn your hatred on someone for this
winding fate of yours, I suggest you focus
that ire on your ＂Sage King＂ Aurelius.
